======================================================================
  Part 1: p(n) FOR ALL TOURNAMENT NUMBERS
======================================================================

Partition function at tournament vocabulary numbers:
  p(KEY1           =    2) =               2 = 2                              ← p(KEY1) = KEY1!!
  p(KEY2           =    3) =               3 = 3                              ← p(KEY2) = KEY2!!
  p(KEY_SUM        =    5) =               7 = 7                              ← p(KEY_SUM) = H_forb_1!!
  p(h(G2)          =    6) =              11 = 11                            
  p(H_forb_1       =    7) =              15 = 3 * 5                         
  p(V(Pet)         =   10) =              42 = 2 * 3 * 7                     
  p(h(E6)          =   12) =              77 = 7 * 11                        
  p(C(6,2)         =   15) =             176 = 2^4 * 11                      
  p(H_forb_2       =   21) =             792 = 2^3 * 3^2 * 11                
  p(|BT|           =   24) =            1575 = 3^2 * 5^2 * 7                 
  p(dim(SO(8))     =   28) =            3718 = 2 * 11 * 13^2                 
  p(h(E8)          =   30) =            5604 = 2^2 * 3 * 467                 
  p(|Phi+(E6)|     =   36) =           17977 = 17977                         
  p(f(9)           =   42) =           53174 = 2 * 11 * 2417                 
  p(|BO|           =   48) =          147273 = 3 * 7 * 7013                  
  p(|Phi+(E7)|     =   63) =         1505499 = 3 * 113 * 4441                
  p(dim(E6)        =   78) =        12132164 = 2^2 * 11 * 103 * 2677         
  p(N(f(w))        =   91) =        64112359 = 29 * 373 * 5927               
  p(|BI|           =  120) =      1844349560 = 2^3 * 5 * 47 * 981037         

  THE PARTITION ENDOMORPHISM:
  p(KEY1) = KEY1 = 2      [FIXED POINT]
  p(KEY2) = KEY2 = 3      [FIXED POINT]
  p(KEY_SUM) = H_forb_1 = 7  [BRIDGE to forbidden!]
  p(h(G2)) = 11           [11th supersingular prime]
  p(H_forb_1) = 15 = C(6,2) [triangular!]
  p(V(Pet)) = 42 = f(9) = h(G2)*H_forb_1  [tournament product!]
  p(h(E6)) = 77 = 7*11 = H_forb_1*11

  The chain: p(2)=2, p(3)=3, p(5)=7, p(7)=15, p(15)=176
  = KEY1 → KEY2 → H_forb_1 → C(6,2) → 176 = KEY1^4*11

  p(10) = 42 = f(9): THE PARTITION COUNT OF V(Pet) = f(9)!!
  This connects V(Petersen) to the polynomial f at 9!

